00:02:00.883 --> 00:02:07.623
child who was male, a son, he would leapfrog both of them in the line of succession.

00:02:08.653 --> 00:02:13.983
What’s more, neither Elizabeth’s father nor mother were on the throne

00:02:14.095 --> 00:02:18.755
when she was born, nor were they directly in line to the throne.

00:02:19.649 --> 00:02:26.359
When she was born, in 1926, her grandfather, King George V, was King of England.

00:02:27.259 --> 00:02:30.009
He had five sons and two daughters.

00:02:30.319 --> 00:02:34.039
His second son, George, was Elizabeth’s father.

00:02:34.999 --> 00:02:42.541
Next in line to the throne in the event of King George V’s death would be his first son, Edward.

00:02:43.506 --> 00:02:49.804
And so it was, when George V died in 1936, when Elizabeth was 10 years

00:02:49.834 --> 00:02:54.834
old, that the throne passed to her uncle, who became Edward VIII.

00:02:55.814 --> 00:02:57.714
He wasn’t to last for long though.

00:02:57.894 --> 00:03:02.914
He was in love with an American lady called Wallis Simpson, who had

00:03:03.044 --> 00:03:07.834
