00:03:38.924 --> 00:03:43.454
throne before, especially for something as trivial as love.

00:03:44.564 --> 00:03:48.814
Elizabeth’s father became king, much to his surprise as well.

00:03:49.414 --> 00:03:55.922
And in an instant, or at least in under a year, Elizabeth went from being a relatively

00:03:56.122 --> 00:04:03.062
minor young royal to being next in line to the throne, aged only 10 years old.

00:04:04.072 --> 00:04:08.602
Even though her father was now king, he was only 40 years old.

00:04:09.662 --> 00:04:14.675
Young, comparatively speaking, and Elizabeth no doubt thought that she would be

00:04:14.685 --> 00:04:21.625
able to live out her childhood in relative obscurity, as a semi-normal person

00:04:21.786 --> 00:04:27.466
before having to take on the duties of queen herself, if that was what was required.

00:04:28.186 --> 00:04:29.236
It wasn’t to be.

00:04:29.986 --> 00:04:36.486
In 1952, after 15 years on the throne, her father died of a blood clot,

00:04:36.856 --> 00:04:41.686
when Elizabeth was only a couple of months away from her 26th birthday.

00:04:42.806 --> 00:04:49.894
Like many men at the time, he had been a heavy smoker and died shortly after his 56th birthday.

00:04:51.007 --> 00:04:56.067
Elizabeth was in Kenya at the time, on a tour with her new husband, Phillip.

00:04:56.557 --> 00:05:00.367
She learned of her father’s death from the local news.

00:05:01.262 --> 00:05:06.452
In an instant all eyes were on her, on this 25 year old girl.

00:05:07.422 --> 00:05:12.132
Up until then, she had lived a relatively secluded life.

00:05:12.322 --> 00:05:19.032
She hadn’t gone to school, and instead had been taught by private tutors at her family home.

00:05:19.752 --> 00:05:25.512
As a young woman, Elizabeth had got married, she had enjoyed time living in Malta with

00:05:25.512 --> 00:05:30.872
her new husband, Prince Phillip, and she had been enjoying life out of the spotlight.

00:05:31.862 --> 00:05:39.242
Her father had been unwell for several years, and had actually had his left lung removed.

00:05:39.816 --> 00:05:44.918
So Elizabeth, in preparation for the day she would become queen,

00:05:45.118 --> 00:05:50.608
reportedly brought black clothes with her wherever she went, just in

00:05:50.608 --> 00:05:55.748
case she received the news and had to change into mourning clothes.

00:05:56.327 --> 00:06:01.767
So she was prepared, from a practical view at least, but no doubt

00:06:02.007 --> 00:06:06.457
there is not much that can really prepare you for life as Queen.

00:06:07.637 --> 00:06:13.157
At her coronation, in 1953, she became the most famous woman in

00:06:13.157 --> 00:06:17.857
the country, and one of the most famous women in the entire world.

00:06:18.777 --> 00:06:23.177
Her face was on the money not only in the UK but in Canada,

00:06:23.217 --> 00:06:28.257
Australia, and all over British colonies in Africa and the Caribbean.

00:06:28.787 --> 00:06:32.267
She was on postage stamps, she was all over the newspapers.

00:06:32.597 --> 00:06:36.357
You could take a picture of the queen to almost any town

00:06:36.377 --> 00:06:40.467
or village in the world and people would know who she was.

00:06:41.497 --> 00:06:46.327
To state the obvious, it must have been an incredible amount of pressure

00:06:46.347 --> 00:06:52.247
for anyone, but especially for someone who had grown up in a tiny bubble.

00:06:53.147 --> 00:06:57.117
Now, let’s quickly reflect on the world, and the country,

00:06:57.197 --> 00:07:01.070
that Elizabeth found when she became queen in 1952.

00:07:02.077 --> 00:07:06.887
The Second World War had finished only 7 years before, there was still

00:07:07.037 --> 00:07:12.477
rationing in Britain, meaning that there were still limits on food and certain

00:07:12.477 --> 00:07:18.387
goods, and indeed the queen used her ration coupons to buy her wedding dress.

00:07:19.387 --> 00:07:24.827
Britain still had colonies all over the world, Europe was rebounding, the

00:07:24.827 --> 00:07:29.987
United States had been fighting in Korea, the Cold War was just getting started.

00:07:31.147 --> 00:07:37.657
By 1952 the process initiated by the first majority Labour government

00:07:37.707 --> 00:07:42.547
in Britain of getting rid of colonies and starting the Commonwealth

00:07:42.587 --> 00:07:48.087
was well underway, and Britain’s empire was firmly on the decline.

00:07:49.227 --> 00:07:55.312
And talking specifically about the British monarchy, the public hated the queen’s

00:07:55.332 --> 00:08:01.952
uncle, Edward VIII for abdicating, and his brother, King George VI had a tough

00:08:01.972 --> 00:08:07.572
job at trying to win back public support and trust in the British monarchy.

00:08:08.318 --> 00:08:12.928
The post-war period was a period of change in the UK.

00:08:13.358 --> 00:08:21.003
People questioned the status quo,  the Labour government introduced heavy taxes on wealth, and

00:08:21.003 --> 00:08:27.143
there were real question marks over whether the UK should have a monarch as its head of state.

00:08:27.983 --> 00:08:33.083
Looking across the Channel, France seemed to be doing ok without a monarch, Italy

00:08:33.243 --> 00:08:38.339
had got rid of its monarch, and let’s not forget that the British people had

00:08:38.349 --> 00:08:43.989
revolted against their monarch before, and executed the king and abolished the

00:08:43.989 --> 00:08:50.889
monarchy in 1649, so it wasn’t a complete impossibility that it could happen again.

00:08:51.619 --> 00:08:56.949
So, when Elizabeth was crowned queen, the UK, its monarchy, and the

00:08:56.949 --> 00:09:02.523
wider world was in a slightly precarious, a difficult, situation.

