00:09:22.194 --> 00:09:26.988
To state the obvious, a lot has happened in those 70 years, in the

00:09:27.018 --> 00:09:31.168
UK, to the world, to the monarchy, and to the queen personally.

00:09:31.908 --> 00:09:35.648
Instead of going through the queen’s life chronologically,

00:09:35.768 --> 00:09:39.018
we are going to focus on three main themes.

00:09:39.968 --> 00:09:45.718
Firstly, her personal life, and how much we know about her as a human being.

00:09:46.538 --> 00:09:51.418
Secondly, how the monarchy has changed with her at its head.

00:09:52.108 --> 00:09:58.827
And thirdly, the controversies she has managed to survive and the problems she has faced.

00:09:59.817 --> 00:10:01.387
So, her personal life.

00:10:02.187 --> 00:10:07.177
It is somewhat of a contradiction that the queen might be one of the most famous

00:10:07.207 --> 00:10:13.497
women in the world, yet we really know very little about her as a human being.

00:10:14.257 --> 00:10:19.487
Throughout the years she has remained mute, silent, on political

00:10:19.487 --> 00:10:24.717
issues, and we really don’t know what she thinks about almost anything.

00:10:25.567 --> 00:10:31.407
People have interpreted various things she has done as being signs of her beliefs,

00:10:31.707 --> 00:10:37.737
for example wearing a hat that looked a little bit like the EU flag was interpreted

00:10:37.977 --> 00:10:43.707
as showing her support of the EU, but we really don’t know what she actually thinks.

00:10:44.807 --> 00:10:50.247
Royal commentators have always commented on her sense of duty and loyalty to

00:10:50.247 --> 00:10:56.767
the crown, and suggested that she wants to remain almost invisible, anonymous,

00:10:56.837 --> 00:11:03.767
because the important thing is what she represents–the British monarchy–and showing

00:11:03.767 --> 00:11:09.057
her personality and true character would get in the way of what she represents.

00:11:10.097 --> 00:11:13.197
We do know a little bit about what she likes.

00:11:13.437 --> 00:11:18.767
In particular, she is a huge fan of a type of dog called a

00:11:18.827 --> 00:11:23.247
Corgi, which is a type of small dog originally from Wales.

00:11:24.089 --> 00:11:29.494
On an interesting linguistic note, the word “corgi” actually comes from the

00:11:29.494 --> 00:11:36.174
Welsh words for “cor”, meaning dwarf, or very small, and “ci”, meaning dog.

00:11:36.664 --> 00:11:40.374
So “corgi” just means “dwarf dog” in Welsh.

00:11:41.084 --> 00:11:48.194
In any case, the Queen loves them, and has had over 30 different corgis over the course of her life.

00:11:48.804 --> 00:11:53.854
They are, reportedly, not very well behaved, and run all over

00:11:53.904 --> 00:11:58.354
Buckingham Palace, sitting on the sofas and generally causing trouble.

00:11:59.074 --> 00:12:04.328
There are all sort of stories about how the Queen does things like drinks a glass of

00:12:04.328 --> 00:12:10.138
champagne every night before bed, and how she has been wearing the same nail polish

00:12:10.358 --> 00:12:18.157
since 1989, but these stories tend to use a lot of “anonymous sources”, and although they

00:12:18.157 --> 00:12:24.037
might make for fun newspaper articles, they’re probably as much fiction as they are fact.

00:12:25.177 --> 00:12:31.767
Our second theme is how the monarchy has changed under her tenure, while she has been queen.

00:12:32.977 --> 00:12:38.077
As far as this is concerned, even the most devout republican would

00:12:38.087 --> 00:12:42.751
have to admit that the Queen has been effective at modernising the

00:12:42.751 --> 00:12:48.521
British monarchy and appealing to the public, both in the UK and abroad.

00:12:49.382 --> 00:12:53.825
She and other members of the Royal Family have made thousands of public

00:12:53.825 --> 00:12:59.855
appearances, visiting hospitals, schools, becoming patrons of charities.

00:13:00.255 --> 00:13:04.915
She has allowed documentaries to be made about the Royal Family, and has

00:13:04.925 --> 00:13:10.805
presented the Royal Family as more accessible and more human than ever before.

00:13:11.745 --> 00:13:17.588
And this is in a large part due to the queen, personally, due to Elizabeth.

00:13:18.228 --> 00:13:23.578
She as an individual is still very popular in the UK and abroad.

00:13:24.348 --> 00:13:31.788
In the UK, recent surveys have around 72% of the population saying that they approve of her.

00:13:32.696 --> 00:13:36.288
She is also hugely popular in America.

00:13:36.778 --> 00:13:43.758
There’s been a national poll in America of the public’s most admired man and women every year.

00:13:44.388 --> 00:13:53.468
