00:14:05.688 --> 00:14:10.548
was asked about Australia becoming a republic, said, about the queen.

00:14:10.948 --> 00:14:15.958
“She's been an extraordinary head of state, and I think frankly, in

00:14:15.988 --> 00:14:20.448
Australia, there are more Elizabethans than there are monarchists”.

00:14:21.185 --> 00:14:25.285
So, he is saying that people in Australia are bigger fans

00:14:25.485 --> 00:14:29.665
of the queen the person than what the queen represents.

00:14:30.575 --> 00:14:36.865
This is somewhat ironic, given how hard the queen tries to hide her personality

00:14:37.025 --> 00:14:42.905
and put all the focus on what she represents, but she would no doubt be happy that

00:14:42.905 --> 00:14:48.325
she is helping solidify the reputation of the monarchy for the next generation.

00:14:49.205 --> 00:14:53.615
It hasn’t, of course, all been simple for the queen, and this

00:14:53.635 --> 00:14:58.895
leads us on to our third part: the controversies and tougher times.

00:15:00.035 --> 00:15:04.135
She has made some bad mistakes, and there have been plenty of

00:15:04.135 --> 00:15:07.715
times when it looked like it would be difficult to come back.

00:15:09.005 --> 00:15:13.415
1992, for example, she called her “annus horribilis”.

00:15:13.725 --> 00:15:18.075
